HEADWORD: Orgeat
<hw>Or"geat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>orge</ets> barley, L. <ets>hordeum</ets>.]</ety> <def>A sirup in
which, formerly, a decoction of barley entered, but which is now
prepared with an emulsion of almonds, -- used to flavor beverages or
edibles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

